name: Ratan Tata
summary: Ratan Tata, the renowned Indian industrialist who led the global expansion of the Tata Group, passed away at the age of 86. As the former chairman of the vast conglomerate, Tata transformed the company into a multinational powerhouse. His legacy extends beyond business, as he was also known for his philanthropy and dedication to the advancement of India's economy and society.

name: Witherspoon
summary: Hollywood star Reese Witherspoon has been busy juggling her professional and personal life. In the world of entertainment, she is gearing up for the highly anticipated third season of "Big Little Lies," which will see the return of the original author. Additionally, Witherspoon is making waves in the business world with her annual Shine Away Conference and the launch of her own wine label. On the personal front, she has reportedly found love with businessman Oliver Haarmann, who accompanied her on a recent outing. Witherspoon has also candidly shared her experiences as a single mother, emphasizing the importance of making decisions for her children's well-being. Meanwhile, the news also highlights the accomplishments of individuals with the same surname: Cortly Witherspoon, who serves as a Care Liaison in Baltimore County, and athlete Layne Witherspoon, a rising star in the world of sports.

name: Tropicana implosion
summary: Las Vegas' Tropicana resort, a Rat Pack-era icon that stood for 67 years, has met its end with an implosion. The demolition made way for a new baseball stadium for the Oakland Athletics. Tourists and news outlets witnessed the spectacle as the implosion cleared the way for the next chapter of the Las Vegas Strip. Many saw the event as the end of an era, marking the passing of an old favorite. Despite its end, the Tropicana will be remembered as a symbol of Las Vegas's golden age and will continue to hold a place in the city's history.

name: Lieutenant Dan
summary: Florida's "Lieutenant Dan," a nickname given to a man living on a sailboat, has gained attention for his decision to stay aboard his vessel during Hurricane Milton, a Category 5 storm. Despite warnings and rescue attempts, the man, who resembles the character from the movie "Forrest Gump," believes that his boat will remain afloat. However, after initial reports that the man had been rescued, the Tampa Mayor later clarified that he was still on his boat. The man's insistence on staying on his vessel, likened to "Noah and his ark," has sparked discussion and concern, prompting authorities to continue efforts to persuade him to seek shelter.

name: Phillies
summary: In a heated playoff series, the New York Mets secured a crucial victory over the Philadelphia Phillies to advance to the National League Championship Series (NLCS). Francisco Lindor's grand slam in Game 4 highlighted the Mets' offensive dominance, while the series marked the 1,082nd meeting between the two rivals and their first in the playoffs. Despite a strong start, the Phillies faltered in Game 3, bringing them to the brink of elimination with a 7-2 loss. The Mets' relentless pressure continued in Game 3, pushing the Phillies to the brink of defeat.

name: Wendy's Krabby Patty
summary: Fast-food giant Wendy's has collaborated with the popular cartoon series SpongeBob SquarePants to create a limited-time Krabby Patty meal. The meal has garnered significant attention, with many eager to try the iconic burger and accompanying items. Reviews of the Krabby Patty Kollab have been mixed, with some praising its clever execution and nostalgic value, while others have expressed disappointment with its execution and flavor. The meal includes the Krabby Patty burger, which features a square-shaped patty, lettuce, tomato, cheese, pickles, and tartar sauce, along with a side of fries and a Frosty dessert. The biggest mystery surrounding the meal is the secret recipe for the Krabby Patty sauce, which Wendy's is keeping closely guarded.

name: Lisa Marie Presley
summary: In Lisa Marie Presley's posthumous memoir, it is revealed that she kept her son Benjamin Keough's body at her home for two months after his death. The memoir also sheds light on Presley's struggles with her father Elvis Presley's death, her relationships, including her marriage to Michael Jackson, and her grief over Benjamin's passing. Riley Keough, Presley's daughter, assisted in completing the memoir using her mother's voice recordings, resulting in a raw and comprehensive account of the family's intergenerational sorrows.
